# Prototype the decision loop on replayed traffic

## Step

Cheapest touchable artifact: a throwaway Fable loop fed a real day of joelclaw message traffic (replayed from the stream/journal, not live), producing what it *would have sent* — rewrites in one voice, storm aggregations, hold/deliver choices with one-line reasons.

This is an alignment instrument, not a cutover gate. Joel ruled out a shadow window; full replacement stands. The prototype exists so Joel can react to the agent's actual judgment and voice before the decision-loop design closes — a reaction beats a discussion.

Standing call (Joel, 2026-07-21): fine with a prototype **as long as it has a clear iteration path to production if it proves out**. So build on the real seams, not a mock rig: replay through the real stream read API (the seam map's paginated replay), package the loop the way the plugin-surface map recommends (Claude plugin), and write decision receipts in the shapes the design will keep. Harness glue and the review surface may be throwaway; the loop core, its tooling, and its prompt files are the seed of the production container. The result section must name the iteration path: what hardens, what gets discarded, what the next slice is.

Joel touches the output (a rendered before/after of a real day) and grills: is the voice right, are the aggregations right, what did it wrongly hold or wrongly deliver.

Resolved when Joel has reacted to at least one full replayed day and the reactions are recorded as design inputs in the result section. Feeds [Design the decision loop](./design-decision-loop.svx) and [Plan the full cutover](./plan-full-cutover.svx).
